FG reopens Kano, Enugu, Port Harcourt airports for international flights The Federal Government has reassured citizens that the AstraZeneca vaccine that is currently being rolled out in Nigeria has been tested and authorized for use because it is safe and efficacious.  The Secretary to the Government of the Federation/Chairman of the Presidential Task force on Covid-19, Mr. Boss Mustapha who gave the assurance in Abuja during the National Briefing noted that this was necessary due to reports from all over the world over the safety and side effects of the AstraZeneca vaccine while affirming that all measures have been put in place to ensure it's safety.  Our correspondent Nathan Williams reports that the Executive Director of the National Primary Health Care Development Agency, DR FAISAL SHUAIB said the AstraZeneca/Oxford COVID-19 vaccines have been distributed to all states and that over 8,000 Nigerians have been administered the vaccine without any official report of serious adverse effects from any of those who have been vaccinated.  Meanwhile the Minister of Aviation, Hadi Sirika, announced during the weekly briefing of the PTF that Kano, Port Harcourt and Enugu airports have been reopened for international flights.Sirika assured that all the things that need to be put in place to ensure smooth and safe operations will be in place before the set dates.‚Äù